WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:10.487 --> 00:00:12.020
Gently.

2
00:00:12.105 --> 00:00:14.906
I can't do this.

3
00:00:14.941 --> 00:00:16.107
Yes. you can.

4
00:00:16.193 --> 00:00:18.409
Feel the layers.

5
00:00:23.116 --> 00:00:27.001
A man's flesh will
give to the blade.

6
00:00:34.261 --> 00:00:35.593
(inhales)

7
00:00:35.629 --> 00:00:38.463
Too much force.

8
00:00:38.515 --> 00:00:40.632
A gentler hand.

9
00:01:00.654 --> 00:01:02.403
(knock at door)

10
00:01:02.489 --> 00:01:05.039
Come.

11
00:01:05.125 --> 00:01:06.457
Morning. my lady.

12
00:01:06.493 --> 00:01:07.742
Good morning.
Isabel.

13
00:01:12.499 --> 00:01:14.332
I think I would like something
with a bit more color.

14
00:01:17.053 --> 00:01:19.387
My mourning time is finished.

15
00:01:19.472 --> 00:01:21.973
Then let's find
something cheerful.

16
00:01:44.998 --> 00:01:46.831
(sniffles)

17
00:02:07.088 --> 00:02:09.688
_

18
00:02:09.689 --> 00:02:11.889
You have never asked me
how I gained these skills.

19
00:02:13.693 --> 00:02:15.960
Are you not curious
about my knowledge

20
00:02:16.029 --> 00:02:17.695
in the remedies
of the body?

21
00:02:17.731 --> 00:02:21.232
I know there are many things
about you to be revealed.

22
00:02:21.284 --> 00:02:23.401
Perhaps I fear the truth
each burden will bring.

23
00:02:23.453 --> 00:02:26.237
Yes.

24
00:02:26.323 --> 00:02:28.823
Sometimes. a past life exposed

25
00:02:28.908 --> 00:02:30.825
can change our living
in the present.

26
00:02:30.910 --> 00:02:33.211
And what of my past life?

27
00:02:34.965 --> 00:02:36.914
Do you know about me?

28
00:02:36.967 --> 00:02:39.050
My secrets?

29
00:02:48.395 --> 00:02:50.762
(grunting)

30
00:02:50.814 --> 00:02:52.730
(grunting continues)

31
00:03:21.211 --> 00:03:23.428
When I was an infant.

32
00:03:23.463 --> 00:03:24.879
a young woman--

33
00:03:24.964 --> 00:03:29.300
a nun--
left me with the monks.

34
00:03:29.352 --> 00:03:31.719
Told them I was fatherless.

35
00:03:34.974 --> 00:03:36.891
Was she my mother?

36
00:03:36.976 --> 00:03:38.893
Yes.

37
00:03:41.314 --> 00:03:43.648
Her journey is finished.

38
00:03:43.700 --> 00:03:45.400
She is gone now

39
00:03:45.485 --> 00:03:48.486
and watches over you
with the angels.

40
00:03:48.571 --> 00:03:51.823
I am sorry. Wilkin.

41
00:03:58.998 --> 00:04:01.249
(Annora sighs)

42
00:04:04.554 --> 00:04:08.005
And how is the boy?

43
00:04:08.058 --> 00:04:09.841
- Lost.
- Hmm.

44
00:04:09.893 --> 00:04:11.426
Full of doubt.

45
00:04:11.511 --> 00:04:12.593
Yea.

46
00:04:15.482 --> 00:04:17.655
(inhales)

47
00:04:18.660 --> 00:04:20.325
As were we.

48
00:04:22.605 --> 00:04:23.688
Yes.

49
00:04:29.329 --> 00:04:31.579
As were we.

50
00:04:34.701 --> 00:04:40.121
♪ born with a heart ♪

51
00:04:40.207 --> 00:04:44.876
♪ that could ache
more than beat ♪

52
00:04:47.080 --> 00:04:53.001
♪ the mind of a killer ♪

53
00:04:53.086 --> 00:04:56.838
♪ the soul of the meek ♪

54
00:04:59.426 --> 00:05:05.013
♪ flock with no shepherd ♪

55
00:05:05.098 --> 00:05:11.135
♪ is a vulnerable game ♪

56
00:05:11.204 --> 00:05:14.022
♪ I can live
without a hearth ♪

57
00:05:14.107 --> 00:05:17.358
♪ without love ♪

58
00:05:17.444 --> 00:05:21.412
♪ but I do need a name ♪

59
00:05:24.117 --> 00:05:26.751
♪ father. do you burn ♪

60
00:05:26.786 --> 00:05:30.288
♪ if your hand is in fire? ♪

61
00:05:30.340 --> 00:05:33.341
♪ does your head
spin with rage ♪

62
00:05:33.426 --> 00:05:36.845
♪ when fooled by the liars? ♪

63
00:05:36.930 --> 00:05:42.433
♪ king of the kings ♪

64
00:05:42.469 --> 00:05:47.105
♪ do you feel any pain? ♪

65
00:05:48.642 --> 00:05:53.206
♪ do you feel any pain? ♪

66
00:05:53.207 --> 00:05:58.303
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

67
00:06:12.036 --> 00:06:14.286
Secured to travel?

68
00:06:18.864 --> 00:06:22.406
_

69
00:06:23.047 --> 00:06:24.246
They approach!

70
00:06:24.298 --> 00:06:25.297
A dozen furlongs.

71
00:06:26.918 --> 00:06:28.668
Wipe that color
from your face. Nia.

72
00:06:28.753 --> 00:06:31.170
I was firm.
You only keep watch.

73
00:06:31.255 --> 00:06:33.422
Watch what? The lot of you
failing without my help?

74
00:06:33.474 --> 00:06:34.640
Enough prattle.

75
00:06:34.726 --> 00:06:35.925
little sister.

76
00:06:36.010 --> 00:06:37.093
Hold yourself here.

77
00:06:38.229 --> 00:06:40.479
(gasps)

78
00:06:43.434 --> 00:06:45.685
I hold for no one.

79
00:06:47.972 --> 00:06:50.106
WILKIN:
<i>We should return to the castle</i>

80
00:06:50.158 --> 00:06:53.109
before the good Chamberlain
wonders where we ride.

81
00:06:53.161 --> 00:06:55.578
Yea.

82
00:06:55.613 --> 00:06:57.947
BERBER:
Good morning.

83
00:06:57.999 --> 00:06:59.865
Morning.
Berber. Calo.

84
00:06:59.951 --> 00:07:01.751
Where's Ash?

85
00:07:01.786 --> 00:07:03.419
CALO:
Our question as well.

86
00:07:03.454 --> 00:07:05.371
He went out for the hunt
yesterday; not shown since.

87
00:07:05.456 --> 00:07:07.256
Ah.

88
00:07:07.291 --> 00:07:09.341
Perhaps he traveled too far.
made camp in midshire.

89
00:07:09.427 --> 00:07:10.760
ANNORA:
If he snares rabbits.

90
00:07:10.795 --> 00:07:13.345
his traps will be to the south.

91
00:07:13.431 --> 00:07:15.881
I have traveled these dead oaks
many times.

92
00:07:15.967 --> 00:07:18.017
Then we venture.
Find the furry poc.

93
00:07:18.102 --> 00:07:19.719
Go well-armed.

94
00:07:19.804 --> 00:07:23.189
These sea caves hide
the banished and thieving.

95
00:07:23.274 --> 00:07:24.807
We also hide like the banished.

96
00:07:24.859 --> 00:07:28.194
all in need of a hasty revenge.

97
00:07:28.279 --> 00:07:30.312
Any gains on finding
the guilty?

98
00:07:30.364 --> 00:07:32.648
We've learned there were
four other knights.

99
00:07:32.734 --> 00:07:34.066
along with our new reeve.

100
00:07:34.152 --> 00:07:35.651
He is the key
to finding the guilty.

101
00:07:35.737 --> 00:07:38.404
Leon Tell led
the company of noble savages

102
00:07:38.489 --> 00:07:40.239
that wracked our village.

103
00:07:40.324 --> 00:07:41.991
Yea. and when we
gain his trust.

104
00:07:42.043 --> 00:07:44.744
we will pry from his lips
the names of the murderers.

105
00:07:44.829 --> 00:07:48.247
My patience may run dry
before his trust sets in.

106
00:07:48.332 --> 00:07:50.332
You gave me
your oath.

107
00:07:50.418 --> 00:07:52.468
Leon torments me.

108
00:07:52.503 --> 00:07:54.754
Petra's cross hung
about his noble neck.

109
00:07:54.839 --> 00:07:57.306
Every glint of that sapphire

110
00:07:57.341 --> 00:07:59.809
mocks my hesitation to plunge
a blade into his heart.

111
00:07:59.844 --> 00:08:01.310
As I want to plunge a blade
into the man

112
00:08:01.345 --> 00:08:02.678
who slaughtered my wife and son.

113
00:08:02.764 --> 00:08:04.563
And for my grandfather.

114
00:08:04.649 --> 00:08:06.899
And my mother. too.
deserves to be avenged.

115
00:08:06.984 --> 00:08:09.068
We all need
to close this pain.

116
00:08:09.153 --> 00:08:12.354
We don't have a proof
of a decorated neck. as you do.

117
00:08:12.406 --> 00:08:15.317
The reeve must stay alive
until we all have our truth.

118
00:08:15.987 --> 00:08:17.757
And would you be able
to hold your rage

119
00:08:17.758 --> 00:08:21.209
if you had certainty of the man
who slit your boy's throat?

120
00:08:21.244 --> 00:08:22.698
ANNORA: Stop this!

121
00:08:22.750 --> 00:08:25.084
The anger is for the guilty.

122
00:08:25.169 --> 00:08:26.335
You need
each other.

123
00:08:31.793 --> 00:08:33.959
At least he listens
to the witch.

124
00:08:41.385 --> 00:08:43.152
Hyah. Hyah!

125
00:08:46.357 --> 00:08:48.357
Noble cowards!

126
00:08:48.392 --> 00:08:49.792
You're on
a fool's errand.

127
00:08:49.861 --> 00:08:50.960
- Yah!
- Yah!

128
00:08:53.030 --> 00:08:54.113
Yah!

129
00:08:54.198 --> 00:08:55.481
(urging horses forward)

130
00:08:56.484 --> 00:08:58.450
(horse neighing)

131
00:08:58.536 --> 00:09:01.287
After them!

132
00:09:01.372 --> 00:09:02.738
Run!

133
00:09:02.824 --> 00:09:05.040
Get back here!

134
00:09:06.577 --> 00:09:07.743
KNIGHT:
Go on!

135
00:09:10.798 --> 00:09:12.548
(cracking)
(neighing)

136
00:09:20.808 --> 00:09:22.842
Shit.

137
00:09:22.927 --> 00:09:24.677
(panting)

138
00:09:24.762 --> 00:09:26.979
(chatter outside)

139
00:09:28.432 --> 00:09:31.350
Where have you been. Maddy?

140
00:09:31.435 --> 00:09:33.903
(fire crackling) _

141
00:09:33.938 --> 00:09:36.155
Marshal and I
had court business.

142
00:09:36.240 --> 00:09:38.407
And what task covers
your boots in clay?

143
00:09:42.446 --> 00:09:45.197
It's best I don't bother you
with the points of my trade.

144
00:09:45.283 --> 00:09:47.700
I've known you since
I was nine. husband.

145
00:09:47.785 --> 00:09:49.668
There's nothing you can say

146
00:09:49.754 --> 00:09:51.287
that would be a bother to me.

147
00:09:51.339 --> 00:09:53.172
(exhales)

148
00:10:02.016 --> 00:10:05.267
I've tried to speak
of this before.

149
00:10:05.303 --> 00:10:07.303
but your devotion
to this farce...

150
00:10:07.355 --> 00:10:09.305
What farce. my love?

151
00:10:12.860 --> 00:10:15.194
I understand the danger

152
00:10:15.279 --> 00:10:19.031
that your generous rescue puts
on you and your children.

153
00:10:19.116 --> 00:10:21.233
But when we are alone.

154
00:10:21.319 --> 00:10:23.485
we can be in the truth
of who I am.

155
00:10:23.537 --> 00:10:25.871
You are my husband.

156
00:10:25.957 --> 00:10:28.240
And I love you deeply.

157
00:10:28.326 --> 00:10:30.826
Is that not
the truth?

158
00:10:30.912 --> 00:10:32.527
(knocking at door)

159
00:10:32.528 --> 00:10:33.528
(sighs)

160
00:10:35.807 --> 00:10:37.210
LUCA:
Father?

161
00:10:43.924 --> 00:10:46.375
Yea?

162
00:10:46.460 --> 00:10:48.293
Services are needed. punisher.

163
00:11:01.892 --> 00:11:04.109
(quiet footsteps)

164
00:11:16.790 --> 00:11:18.824
The color of your dress
would suggest

165
00:11:18.909 --> 00:11:22.244
it is time for less...
weighted thought.

166
00:11:23.747 --> 00:11:26.832
No thoughts of weight.
just distance.

167
00:11:26.917 --> 00:11:29.051
I travel to Windsor
in two weeks' time.

168
00:11:29.086 --> 00:11:31.637
summoned by
His Majesty.

169
00:11:31.722 --> 00:11:35.090
I assume to receive guidance
on how we govern.

170
00:11:35.176 --> 00:11:38.010
Or. perhaps.
to offer condolences.

171
00:11:38.095 --> 00:11:41.096
We often find
much of ourselves

172
00:11:41.182 --> 00:11:42.931
in the grief
of others.

173
00:11:50.407 --> 00:11:53.692
God has a plan
for this noble woman.

174
00:11:56.830 --> 00:11:59.665
Stay inside your truth.
Lady Love.

175
00:11:59.750 --> 00:12:02.701
I am afraid that is a very

176
00:12:02.786 --> 00:12:05.537
uncomfortable place.
dear Father.

177
00:12:05.623 --> 00:12:07.456
(door opens)

178
00:12:09.510 --> 00:12:11.543
Pardon. Baroness.

179
00:12:11.629 --> 00:12:13.712
There's been another
act of rebellion.

180
00:12:13.797 --> 00:12:15.547
Byth Encil.

181
00:12:15.633 --> 00:12:17.432
The effigy
of your husband.

182
00:12:17.468 --> 00:12:20.385
attacked
on the north forest trail.

183
00:12:20.471 --> 00:12:22.771
Children
with yellow-painted faces.

184
00:12:22.806 --> 00:12:24.473
LOCKE: We've captured
one of the offenders.

185
00:12:24.525 --> 00:12:25.691
A girl.

186
00:12:25.776 --> 00:12:26.725
Not yet 16.

187
00:12:26.810 --> 00:12:28.227
Could it not just be

188
00:12:28.312 --> 00:12:30.145
the foolishness of youth?

189
00:12:30.231 --> 00:12:31.446
Painting
their faces.

190
00:12:31.482 --> 00:12:34.199
acting like
their misguided heroes?

191
00:12:34.285 --> 00:12:36.034
Foolishness or not.

192
00:12:36.120 --> 00:12:38.820
it will be perceived
as an act of treason.

193
00:12:38.872 --> 00:12:40.956
Penalty of death.

194
00:12:40.991 --> 00:12:45.327
I pray you stay mindful.
my lady.

195
00:12:45.379 --> 00:12:47.579
With our baron's passing.
all eyes are on us.

196
00:12:47.665 --> 00:12:49.167
from London
to Pryceshire.

197
00:12:49.168 --> 00:12:52.336
We must make swift.
sound and strong decisions.

198
00:12:52.337 --> 00:12:53.337
I believe that
all my decisions

199
00:12:53.338 --> 00:12:55.380
are made with
those intentions.

200
00:12:55.415 --> 00:12:57.139
Indeed.

201
00:12:58.592 --> 00:13:00.058
Where is
the girl from?

202
00:13:00.144 --> 00:13:01.476
She is a most
stubborn thing. Baroness.

203
00:13:01.512 --> 00:13:03.061
She gives up nothing.

204
00:13:03.147 --> 00:13:04.313
The punisher's
been summoned.

205
00:13:04.348 --> 00:13:06.565
He will find ways
to break her silence.

206
00:13:06.650 --> 00:13:08.183
I will speak to the girl

207
00:13:08.269 --> 00:13:10.519
before anyone breaks anything.

208
00:13:10.571 --> 00:13:12.404
Baroness.

209
00:13:20.331 --> 00:13:22.164
(door closes)

210
00:13:31.775 --> 00:13:33.759
- (horse snorts)
ANNORA: - Whoa. _

211
00:13:33.844 --> 00:13:35.277
CALO: There's another one
of Ash's traps.

212
00:13:35.346 --> 00:13:37.379
ANNORA: Come on.
(clicks tongue)

213
00:13:37.464 --> 00:13:40.182
These beasts
have all been maimed.

214
00:13:42.720 --> 00:13:44.219
BERBER:
Wolves?

215
00:13:44.305 --> 00:13:46.555
(Annora sighs. clicks tongue)

216
00:13:51.195 --> 00:13:53.562
(insects buzzing)

217
00:13:57.451 --> 00:13:59.901
This wasn't wolves.

218
00:13:59.953 --> 00:14:01.320
(neighs)

219
00:14:08.981 --> 00:14:09.981
_

220
00:14:09.982 --> 00:14:12.867
LEON: The Byth Encil
starts them young.

221
00:14:12.952 --> 00:14:15.619
We need to know who she is

222
00:14:15.655 --> 00:14:17.571
and where the
other rebels are.

223
00:14:20.209 --> 00:14:22.626
Open the cage.

224
00:14:29.602 --> 00:14:32.353
LEON: You'll need more
than a persuasive tongue.

225
00:14:32.439 --> 00:14:34.439
Pull the fingernails.

226
00:14:34.524 --> 00:14:36.407
The pear will be quicker.

227
00:14:39.195 --> 00:14:41.996
(men chuckle)

228
00:14:42.081 --> 00:14:44.415
LUCA:
I'll-- I'll get it. Father.

229
00:14:50.423 --> 00:14:52.757
With haste.

230
00:14:59.299 --> 00:15:00.848
(door creaks closed)

231
00:15:07.056 --> 00:15:08.890
You stick it in her slot.

232
00:15:11.561 --> 00:15:14.645
God in heaven.

233
00:15:27.710 --> 00:15:30.545
Listen to me. child.

234
00:15:30.630 --> 00:15:32.046
You need to tell
them what you know.

235
00:15:32.131 --> 00:15:33.464
This isn't a game.

236
00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:34.632
(spits)

237
00:15:36.135 --> 00:15:39.170
They want me
to torture you.

238
00:15:39.255 --> 00:15:41.088
bring unbearable pain.

239
00:15:43.092 --> 00:15:46.093
I will get your truth.

240
00:15:46.179 --> 00:15:50.014
Don't make me
do it that way.

241
00:15:50.066 --> 00:15:52.016
You don't know truth.

242
00:15:52.068 --> 00:15:55.019
Mine or anyone's.

243
00:15:55.104 --> 00:15:56.938
We've no choice. brother.

244
00:16:15.542 --> 00:16:18.918
LEON: The punisher is
with her. Chamberlain.

245
00:16:18.919 --> 00:16:19.919
The baroness wants
no harm done

246
00:16:19.920 --> 00:16:20.920
until she speaks
with the girl.

247
00:16:20.921 --> 00:16:21.921
(Nia screams)

248
00:16:23.216 --> 00:16:25.049
Oh. well.

249
00:16:25.134 --> 00:16:27.218
I guess we blame the new reeve.

250
00:16:27.270 --> 00:16:29.437
Yeah. and we know how well
that went for the last one.

251
00:16:32.392 --> 00:16:34.475
I have 17.
Is that enough...

252
00:16:36.529 --> 00:16:38.563
Twins.

253
00:16:38.615 --> 00:16:40.531
A condolence gift
from the king.

254
00:16:40.567 --> 00:16:43.784
along with six
horses and a baker.

255
00:16:45.538 --> 00:16:47.371
Twins.

256
00:16:47.423 --> 00:16:49.256
That will be fun.

257
00:16:51.761 --> 00:16:53.260
This one.
however...

258
00:16:53.346 --> 00:16:55.713
not so much.

259
00:16:55.765 --> 00:16:57.214
Baroness.

260
00:16:57.266 --> 00:16:59.183
(door opens)

261
00:17:04.891 --> 00:17:06.223
The Chamberlain
delivered your need

262
00:17:06.309 --> 00:17:08.025
after we had begun.
my lady.

263
00:17:08.060 --> 00:17:09.860
We ceased immediately.

264
00:17:09.896 --> 00:17:11.612
Deepest apologies.

265
00:17:23.326 --> 00:17:25.159
I need a private moment.

266
00:17:50.603 --> 00:17:52.436
Do you know who I am?

267
00:17:55.825 --> 00:17:58.025
Then you hold the advantage.

268
00:17:58.110 --> 00:17:59.944
I do not even know
what to call you.

269
00:18:03.199 --> 00:18:05.950
Giving me your name
will bring no harm to anyone.

270
00:18:16.128 --> 00:18:17.962
I can't tell you anything.

271
00:18:20.099 --> 00:18:22.549
You can torture me if you want.

272
00:18:25.354 --> 00:18:28.305
What I want is the truth.

273
00:18:28.357 --> 00:18:30.190
Why did you attack our wagon?

274
00:18:32.361 --> 00:18:34.210
Was it a childish dare?

275
00:18:35.272 --> 00:18:39.242
Or are these rebel colors
on your face your true purpose?

276
00:18:39.276 --> 00:18:43.113
The Byth Encil will
take back our country.

277
00:18:44.481 --> 00:18:47.350
What is it that
you want for Wales?

278
00:18:52.455 --> 00:18:55.457
I want it to be quiet.

279
00:18:58.328 --> 00:19:00.329
As do I.

280
00:19:05.869 --> 00:19:09.171
I will have someone tend
to that finger.

281
00:19:21.617 --> 00:19:22.851
Did she confide?

282
00:19:22.885 --> 00:19:25.854
No. she's hardened
in her silence.

283
00:19:25.888 --> 00:19:27.856
The we apply harsh measures

284
00:19:27.890 --> 00:19:29.858
until her words spill
more than blood.

285
00:19:29.892 --> 00:19:32.293
Words rarely give
truth. Chamberlain.

286
00:19:32.327 --> 00:19:35.830
One must be aware of all the
other things that speak to us.

287
00:19:37.699 --> 00:19:39.667
Her dress is
salt-washed and waxed.

288
00:19:39.701 --> 00:19:42.503
Her skin red with the burn
of coastal winds.

289
00:19:42.537 --> 00:19:44.139
She's from a fishing village.

290
00:19:44.173 --> 00:19:46.141
If you caught her
on the north trail.

291
00:19:46.175 --> 00:19:49.210
it is most likely
Penfras Mawr.

292
00:19:51.647 --> 00:19:52.846
Very impressive. my lady.

293
00:19:52.881 --> 00:19:55.682
Very simple. good Chamberlain.

294
00:19:55.716 --> 00:19:57.785
Assemble a caravan.

295
00:19:57.819 --> 00:20:00.187
fair number of knights.

296
00:20:00.221 --> 00:20:03.190
I want to go to the village.
find her family.

297
00:20:03.224 --> 00:20:06.126
If they can make recompense.
we can spare the girl.

298
00:20:06.161 --> 00:20:10.130
You should let our soldiers
bring the family here. Baroness.

299
00:20:10.165 --> 00:20:12.666
Your safety is imperative.

300
00:20:12.700 --> 00:20:15.669
The risk is too severe to
leave in God's hands alone.

301
00:20:15.703 --> 00:20:19.239
Then we shall bring the good
priest and Master Gawain.

302
00:20:19.241 --> 00:20:21.208
Clergy and a punisher.

303
00:20:21.242 --> 00:20:23.210
All hands will
be with us.

304
00:20:23.278 --> 00:20:25.244
(chuckles)

305
00:20:31.185 --> 00:20:33.186
(birds chirping.
insets buzzing)

306
00:20:58.212 --> 00:21:00.246
(insects buzzing)

307
00:21:07.354 --> 00:21:09.788
(sizzling)

308
00:21:24.270 --> 00:21:26.271
(snake hisses)

309
00:21:30.809 --> 00:21:32.643
<i>Ecce...</i>

310
00:21:32.678 --> 00:21:35.646
<i>Crúcem Dómini.</i>

311
00:21:35.681 --> 00:21:39.149
<i>fúgite pártes adversae.</i>

312
00:21:39.184 --> 00:21:41.552
(snake hissing)

313
00:21:54.524 --> 00:21:56.425
Mother.

314
00:21:56.459 --> 00:21:59.094
Nobles are here. looking
for the family of a young girl

315
00:21:59.128 --> 00:22:00.930
caught attacking one
of the baron's wagons

316
00:22:00.964 --> 00:22:02.230
with a painted face.

317
00:22:02.265 --> 00:22:04.733
Has to be Nia.

318
00:22:04.768 --> 00:22:07.002
I didn't know they caught her.

319
00:22:07.037 --> 00:22:08.470
Piss-witted fool.

320
00:22:08.505 --> 00:22:10.472
I...

321
00:22:10.507 --> 00:22:13.075
I wanted to prove
myself. Mother.

322
00:22:13.109 --> 00:22:14.876
- Nia wasn't supposed...
- Hold your tongue.

323
00:22:19.282 --> 00:22:21.083
Ride to our friends.

324
00:22:21.117 --> 00:22:22.518
Have them tell the Wolf
we need help.

325
00:22:22.552 --> 00:22:24.386
Yea.

326
00:22:24.421 --> 00:22:26.822
Take the catch
to the village.

327
00:22:28.825 --> 00:22:30.158
I'm sorry. Mother.

328
00:22:30.192 --> 00:22:32.995
That noble waif is
the only thing stopping me

329
00:22:33.029 --> 00:22:34.563
from gutting you
like a cod.

330
00:22:55.985 --> 00:22:59.353
Baroness. what brings you
to our simple village?

331
00:22:59.388 --> 00:23:01.990
I'll not waste
your working daylight

332
00:23:02.024 --> 00:23:03.391
telling you things
you already know.

333
00:23:03.425 --> 00:23:04.826
So what then?

334
00:23:04.860 --> 00:23:06.627
Your brawn are here
to punish us?

335
00:23:06.661 --> 00:23:08.196
No.

336
00:23:08.230 --> 00:23:10.365
To offer fair trade.

337
00:23:10.399 --> 00:23:13.301
We will spare
your daughter's life

338
00:23:13.335 --> 00:23:15.336
if you give us something
in return.

339
00:23:15.371 --> 00:23:19.740
Oh. you can have all I possess--
fish and poverty.

340
00:23:22.010 --> 00:23:24.378
I wish to meet
this rebel leader.

341
00:23:24.413 --> 00:23:26.280
the one you call the Wolf.

342
00:23:29.384 --> 00:23:31.351
LADY LOVE:
Can you arrange that?

343
00:23:31.386 --> 00:23:33.320
CORBETT:
Baroness.

344
00:23:33.354 --> 00:23:37.524
I want to understand
his need for revolution.

345
00:23:37.559 --> 00:23:41.696
what inspires him. perhaps find
a peaceful solution.

346
00:23:43.065 --> 00:23:46.033
I will not waste
your leisure daylight

347
00:23:46.068 --> 00:23:49.036
telling you things
you already know.

348
00:23:49.071 --> 00:23:52.806
I do not know this Wolf.

349
00:23:54.676 --> 00:23:57.678
You're willing to sacrifice
the life of your child?

350
00:24:02.016 --> 00:24:04.418
That's one less mouth to feed.

351
00:24:06.488 --> 00:24:08.322
Are you finished.
my lady?

352
00:24:12.394 --> 00:24:16.329
Your eyes remain hard. but
I know your heart struggles.

353
00:24:16.364 --> 00:24:20.167
And what of your heart.
Lowry Love Aberffraw?

354
00:24:20.201 --> 00:24:21.768
Does it struggle?

355
00:24:21.802 --> 00:24:24.971
The daughter of a
beloved Welsh lord.

356
00:24:25.005 --> 00:24:26.806
lying next to English war dogs.

357
00:24:26.840 --> 00:24:27.840
LEON:
Insolence.

358
00:24:27.875 --> 00:24:29.876
No.

359
00:24:31.879 --> 00:24:34.281
What I have done...

360
00:24:34.315 --> 00:24:39.084
what I do from here forth is
driven by only one intention--

361
00:24:39.119 --> 00:24:42.955
to stop the bloodshed
and oppression of my people.

362
00:24:44.991 --> 00:24:47.960
I do not understand
your hatred of me.

363
00:24:47.994 --> 00:24:51.397
And clearly you do not
understand my love for you.

364
00:25:07.113 --> 00:25:10.482
My lady.
the boy there.

365
00:25:10.517 --> 00:25:13.318
seems he caught his mother's
wrath as we rode in.

366
00:25:13.353 --> 00:25:15.521
Perhaps he knows
of something.

367
00:25:15.555 --> 00:25:17.889
Don't trouble
the baroness

368
00:25:17.924 --> 00:25:20.959
with the whims
of a child. executioner.

369
00:25:20.994 --> 00:25:23.629
But if the boy holds
some knowledge

370
00:25:23.663 --> 00:25:26.064
of rebel movements.

371
00:25:26.099 --> 00:25:28.900
it would allow his sister
a lesser sentence.

372
00:25:28.935 --> 00:25:30.936
Yes. manor law
would allow that.

373
00:25:32.872 --> 00:25:35.306
Please. see what the boy knows.

374
00:25:52.692 --> 00:25:54.659
What's your name?

375
00:25:54.694 --> 00:25:57.128
Mabon.

376
00:25:57.163 --> 00:25:59.798
That didn't take much.

377
00:25:59.832 --> 00:26:02.100
I ripped out your
sister's fingernail;

378
00:26:02.134 --> 00:26:03.935
she still didn't
give us her name.

379
00:26:03.969 --> 00:26:06.437
Is it only the women in your
family that hang with balls?

380
00:26:08.473 --> 00:26:11.843
Do you know what will happen
to your little sister?

381
00:26:11.877 --> 00:26:14.813
Manor law says she
must be put to death.

382
00:26:14.847 --> 00:26:16.947
Treason.

383
00:26:16.982 --> 00:26:18.649
I told her to stay.

384
00:26:18.683 --> 00:26:19.984
TORAN:
But she got caught

385
00:26:20.018 --> 00:26:21.385
because you didn't protect her.

386
00:26:21.419 --> 00:26:23.921
- She's a child.
WILKIN: - Indeed.

387
00:26:23.955 --> 00:26:26.456
And you can save her.

388
00:26:26.491 --> 00:26:29.126
Be the big brother she needs.

389
00:26:32.864 --> 00:26:35.900
If we give the baroness

390
00:26:35.934 --> 00:26:37.567
some tellings
of the rebels--

391
00:26:37.602 --> 00:26:40.271
any movement or plans--

392
00:26:40.305 --> 00:26:42.973
it will save your sister
from my ax.

393
00:26:43.007 --> 00:26:45.242
I don't know anything.

394
00:26:45.276 --> 00:26:47.410
TORAN:
Then you are a coward

395
00:26:47.444 --> 00:26:50.613
for letting a girl take
the blade for your mistake.

396
00:26:52.416 --> 00:26:55.152
Let her death haunt your soul.

397
00:27:00.357 --> 00:27:02.793
If-- if I tell of something...

398
00:27:06.096 --> 00:27:08.565
will you keep that truth
from my mother?

399
00:27:08.599 --> 00:27:12.135
I'll say it came
from some other village.

400
00:27:18.008 --> 00:27:21.177
Don't make us cut it
from your lips.

401
00:27:22.980 --> 00:27:25.448
At the entrance
of our village...

402
00:27:25.483 --> 00:27:27.283
down trail.

403
00:27:27.317 --> 00:27:30.019
there are three smoke hovels.

404
00:27:30.054 --> 00:27:33.022
The third contains no fish.

405
00:27:33.057 --> 00:27:36.226
The rebels store supplies
and weapons there.

406
00:27:36.260 --> 00:27:38.694
Good lad.

407
00:27:38.729 --> 00:27:42.398
You have our word no one
will know it came from you.

408
00:27:50.808 --> 00:27:53.509
Gruffudd will learn
of our presence here.

409
00:27:53.544 --> 00:27:57.113
Our reeve already
delivers the news.

410
00:27:57.147 --> 00:27:59.115
Get word to the Wolf.

411
00:27:59.149 --> 00:28:01.684
Tell him of our need
to save the girl.

412
00:28:01.719 --> 00:28:04.687
Perhaps he'll have more
compassion than her mother.

413
00:28:04.722 --> 00:28:07.557
I'll secure him
more weapons and goods.

414
00:28:07.591 --> 00:28:09.959
He has my word.

415
00:28:15.283 --> 00:28:17.196
CALO:
I've caught our meal.

416
00:28:20.429 --> 00:28:22.430
Where are your thousand loaves?

417
00:28:23.566 --> 00:28:25.534
I assume
you encountered

418
00:28:25.568 --> 00:28:27.803
a miracle being as you return
with enough fish

419
00:28:27.837 --> 00:28:29.905
for a legion of men.

420
00:28:29.939 --> 00:28:32.374
I have a deep hunger
in the morning.

421
00:28:32.408 --> 00:28:35.577
I will collect deeper wood.

422
00:28:41.984 --> 00:28:44.353
(praying quietly)

423
00:28:56.232 --> 00:28:58.233
(branch snaps)

424
00:29:07.142 --> 00:29:09.610
Calo has returned with our meal.

425
00:29:12.047 --> 00:29:13.714
It will require

426
00:29:13.748 --> 00:29:17.318
a week's worth of wood.

427
00:29:19.587 --> 00:29:23.257
What you have seen...

428
00:29:23.292 --> 00:29:25.226
word of it...

429
00:29:25.260 --> 00:29:28.296
Your devotion is your concern.

430
00:29:35.469 --> 00:29:38.638
Even if that devotion
is seen as heresy?

431
00:29:38.672 --> 00:29:42.075
God answers to many
names. good Moor.

432
00:29:42.110 --> 00:29:44.044
Only the fearful
and the ignorant

433
00:29:44.078 --> 00:29:46.880
attempt to judge which
is right and wrong.

434
00:29:46.915 --> 00:29:50.117
What of your devotion.
Annora?

435
00:29:50.151 --> 00:29:52.319
Your way with nature

436
00:29:52.353 --> 00:29:55.621
leans towards a pagan faith.

437
00:29:57.424 --> 00:30:00.126
"My Lord hath given me

438
00:30:00.160 --> 00:30:02.728
a way that is straight.

439
00:30:02.763 --> 00:30:04.964
a religion of right.

440
00:30:04.999 --> 00:30:07.867
the path that is true in faith."

441
00:30:07.902 --> 00:30:11.804
From the scripture
of the king's god?

442
00:30:14.140 --> 00:30:15.941
No.

443
00:30:15.976 --> 00:30:19.745
Your book-- Quran.

444
00:30:19.779 --> 00:30:23.615
Chapter six. verse 161.

445
00:30:33.326 --> 00:30:35.694
(hoofbeats approaching)

446
00:30:44.404 --> 00:30:46.405
(man whistles)

447
00:30:48.441 --> 00:30:50.508
(horses neighing)

448
00:30:50.543 --> 00:30:52.009
(men yelling)

449
00:30:52.044 --> 00:30:52.877
Rebels!

450
00:30:52.911 --> 00:30:54.979
Protect the baroness!

451
00:30:55.013 --> 00:30:56.147
Get her safe!

452
00:30:56.181 --> 00:30:59.050
(grunting)

453
00:31:00.786 --> 00:31:03.555
My lady.

454
00:31:03.589 --> 00:31:04.856
(grunting)

455
00:31:09.094 --> 00:31:11.095
(yells)

456
00:31:17.569 --> 00:31:19.871
(men yelling)

457
00:31:25.978 --> 00:31:27.444
Take this.

458
00:31:31.415 --> 00:31:33.616
(shouting)

459
00:31:46.230 --> 00:31:48.231
(yelling)

460
00:32:02.612 --> 00:32:04.981
(yells)

461
00:32:28.538 --> 00:32:29.904
(grunts)

462
00:32:34.076 --> 00:32:36.044
Are you harmed?

463
00:32:36.078 --> 00:32:37.813
Um...

464
00:32:37.847 --> 00:32:39.715
my nerves are a shudder.

465
00:32:39.749 --> 00:32:41.750
but. no. I am not harmed.

466
00:32:48.324 --> 00:32:51.025
I thank you.

467
00:32:51.059 --> 00:32:52.760
Master Gawain.

468
00:32:55.197 --> 00:32:56.997
CORBETT:
Baroness!

469
00:32:59.368 --> 00:33:03.070
Thanks for that swift blade.
Marshal.

470
00:33:07.242 --> 00:33:08.843
CORBETT:
My lady.

471
00:33:10.878 --> 00:33:12.446
Thank God you are safe.
Baroness.

472
00:33:12.480 --> 00:33:13.714
And you and my knights?

473
00:33:13.748 --> 00:33:16.149
Several injured.
no fatal wounds.

474
00:33:16.184 --> 00:33:17.951
LADY LOVE:
Good.

475
00:33:17.985 --> 00:33:20.187
Well. I believe that
is a sufficient amount

476
00:33:20.221 --> 00:33:23.957
of excitement for one day.

477
00:33:23.991 --> 00:33:25.959
Night falls quickly.

478
00:33:25.993 --> 00:33:27.194
Indeed. my lady.

479
00:33:27.228 --> 00:33:28.729
Let us travel.

480
00:33:28.763 --> 00:33:31.130
Come on.

481
00:33:37.471 --> 00:33:39.439
My lady.

482
00:33:39.473 --> 00:33:41.874
LADY LOVE:
Thank you.

483
00:33:49.785 --> 00:33:52.854
Are you sure you won't eat
anything heartier. my lady?

484
00:33:52.888 --> 00:33:55.957
This is fine. thank you.

485
00:33:55.991 --> 00:33:57.692
One never knows when
they'll need the strength

486
00:33:57.726 --> 00:33:59.160
to fight off more rebels.

487
00:34:01.763 --> 00:34:03.932
You cannot take those
kinds of risks. my lady.

488
00:34:03.966 --> 00:34:06.066
It's lunacy.

489
00:34:06.101 --> 00:34:08.869
Do you remember that
I had a mother. Isabel?

490
00:34:08.904 --> 00:34:11.606
Of course.
A lovely one.

491
00:34:11.640 --> 00:34:13.741
I'm relieved.

492
00:34:13.776 --> 00:34:15.209
I thought. perhaps.
you woke up this morning

493
00:34:15.243 --> 00:34:17.178
and thought that you were her.

494
00:34:17.212 --> 00:34:19.747
It is my duty to see
to your well-being. Love.

495
00:34:19.782 --> 00:34:21.015
(door closes)

496
00:34:21.049 --> 00:34:22.049
(quiet laugh)

497
00:34:22.083 --> 00:34:24.852
Good morning. my lady.

498
00:34:24.886 --> 00:34:26.854
May I have your ear
for a moment?

499
00:34:26.888 --> 00:34:29.089
You may.
good Chamberlain.

500
00:34:29.124 --> 00:34:31.725
I'll meet you in
the garden. Mother.

501
00:34:36.064 --> 00:34:37.698
We have found the
supplies and weapons

502
00:34:37.732 --> 00:34:39.700
the rebels hid in Penfras Mawr.

503
00:34:39.734 --> 00:34:41.735
Good.

504
00:34:41.770 --> 00:34:43.437
We can spare the girl's life.

505
00:34:45.407 --> 00:34:48.509
An agreement made before
the rebels attacked. my lady.

506
00:34:48.543 --> 00:34:50.744
A new level of impiety.

507
00:34:50.779 --> 00:34:53.214
where your life
was put in peril.

508
00:34:53.248 --> 00:34:57.151
Anything less than her head
sends a message of weakness.

509
00:34:57.185 --> 00:34:59.920
And trust that I. indeed.
feel the weight

510
00:34:59.954 --> 00:35:02.756
of all that I put
at risk. Milus.

511
00:35:05.126 --> 00:35:07.694
I will give it deep thought.

512
00:35:14.035 --> 00:35:16.270
Is something else
weighing on you?

513
00:35:16.304 --> 00:35:18.605
Yes. Baroness.

514
00:35:18.639 --> 00:35:20.373
As to the point of the rebels.

515
00:35:20.408 --> 00:35:23.043
your demands yesterday.

516
00:35:23.077 --> 00:35:26.246
Were you in earnest
about meeting this Wolf?

517
00:35:26.281 --> 00:35:28.248
I'm always earnest. Milus.

518
00:35:28.283 --> 00:35:30.684
Baroness. at this
very moment.

519
00:35:30.718 --> 00:35:34.655
our king is deciding
the fate of Ventrishire.

520
00:35:34.689 --> 00:35:38.558
If he deems your actions
to be guided by...

521
00:35:38.593 --> 00:35:40.260
feminine frivolity

522
00:35:40.295 --> 00:35:41.728
or Welsh leanings...

523
00:35:41.763 --> 00:35:43.730
They are not.

524
00:35:43.765 --> 00:35:45.231
No. of course not.

525
00:35:45.266 --> 00:35:47.834
But I must ask.
as your trusted advisor.

526
00:35:47.868 --> 00:35:49.736
that you allow me
to give counsel

527
00:35:49.771 --> 00:35:51.004
before making decisions

528
00:35:51.038 --> 00:35:53.973
that could lead
to deep regret.

529
00:35:54.007 --> 00:35:56.509
The baron always
gave me his ear.

530
00:35:58.845 --> 00:36:02.415
I so appreciate
that wisdom. Milus.

531
00:36:02.449 --> 00:36:06.352
but as you know.
I am not my husband.

532
00:36:08.955 --> 00:36:11.758
Thank you for your counsel.

533
00:36:17.631 --> 00:36:19.832
(door opens)

534
00:36:19.867 --> 00:36:23.069
(quiet footsteps)

535
00:36:23.303 --> 00:36:26.572
It gives me comfort seeing you
on this pew every morning.

536
00:36:26.606 --> 00:36:29.508
Benefits run both ways.

537
00:36:29.542 --> 00:36:32.878
I know it is beyond Lent.

538
00:36:32.912 --> 00:36:36.048
but I'm always here
if you need examination.

539
00:36:36.083 --> 00:36:38.951
Thank you. but. um.

540
00:36:38.986 --> 00:36:41.420
I'm afraid my sins

541
00:36:41.455 --> 00:36:44.790
are between God
and my conscience. Father.

542
00:36:51.197 --> 00:36:54.199
You know where to find me if
you have a change of heart.

543
00:36:56.069 --> 00:36:59.271
Strong hand for a learned man.

544
00:36:59.305 --> 00:37:03.575
I've never seen a priest
wield a mace like that before.

545
00:37:03.609 --> 00:37:05.410
It wasn't learned
at the seminary.

546
00:37:05.445 --> 00:37:06.878
(door opens)

547
00:37:06.912 --> 00:37:10.215
We all have a past life.
good Maddy.

548
00:37:17.423 --> 00:37:19.190
Good morning. my lady.

549
00:37:19.224 --> 00:37:21.426
Father.

550
00:37:26.231 --> 00:37:28.066
Baroness.

551
00:37:28.100 --> 00:37:29.233
(door closes)

552
00:37:29.268 --> 00:37:31.235
I trust you've rested well

553
00:37:31.270 --> 00:37:33.704
after yesterday's excitement.

554
00:37:33.739 --> 00:37:36.106
I have. thank you.

555
00:37:47.719 --> 00:37:49.921
Your way with a sword
is exceptional.

556
00:37:49.955 --> 00:37:52.490
I would venture to say
you are more skilled

557
00:37:52.524 --> 00:37:54.858
than my most honored knights.

558
00:37:54.893 --> 00:37:57.461
(laughs)

559
00:37:57.495 --> 00:38:01.398
Handling a blade is. uh.
a task of my trade.

560
00:38:01.433 --> 00:38:04.134
Swinging an ax to punish

561
00:38:04.168 --> 00:38:06.470
is brutish.

562
00:38:06.504 --> 00:38:09.606
What I witnessed
was refined swordsmanship.

563
00:38:13.377 --> 00:38:15.378
(quiet laugh)

564
00:38:16.881 --> 00:38:20.016
You are a mystery to me.
Master Gawain.

565
00:38:24.688 --> 00:38:28.057
As I am to myself. my lady.

566
00:38:28.091 --> 00:38:30.092
(quiet laugh)

567
00:38:34.498 --> 00:38:37.233
My decision.

568
00:38:37.267 --> 00:38:39.668
The girl.

569
00:38:43.874 --> 00:38:47.543
A judgment
forced by obligation.

570
00:39:05.696 --> 00:39:08.297
(door opens)

571
00:39:08.331 --> 00:39:10.065
(door closes)

572
00:39:16.573 --> 00:39:18.974
(sighs)

573
00:39:43.333 --> 00:39:47.002
Do you show yourself
to help me...

574
00:39:47.036 --> 00:39:49.071
or to haunt me?

575
00:39:49.105 --> 00:39:51.273
We are given that choice

576
00:39:51.307 --> 00:39:54.576
with every encounter. my love.

577
00:39:54.610 --> 00:39:56.378
You must decide.

578
00:39:58.681 --> 00:40:00.648
I'm so sorry.

579
00:40:05.254 --> 00:40:07.889
I was brought to my end

580
00:40:07.923 --> 00:40:09.457
at the right time

581
00:40:09.491 --> 00:40:11.259
for the right reason.

582
00:40:11.293 --> 00:40:14.195
How do I do this?

583
00:40:14.229 --> 00:40:18.299
When you stop looking
for all that is wrong. Wilkin.

584
00:40:18.333 --> 00:40:21.635
you will see that what is right

585
00:40:21.669 --> 00:40:23.804
was just in your grasp.

586
00:40:32.848 --> 00:40:34.849
(sighs)

587
00:40:43.325 --> 00:40:45.759
(sighs heavily)

588
00:41:00.208 --> 00:41:02.575
(crinkling)

589
00:41:10.251 --> 00:41:12.119
(hissing)

590
00:41:15.656 --> 00:41:18.058
(hissing)

591
00:41:25.065 --> 00:41:26.733
(hissing)

592
00:41:31.639 --> 00:41:34.073
(snarls)

593
00:41:34.108 --> 00:41:35.375
(screams)

594
00:41:37.578 --> 00:41:39.379
(screams)

595
00:41:39.413 --> 00:41:41.414
(gasping)

596
00:41:45.953 --> 00:41:48.354
(shuddering breath)

597
00:41:49.756 --> 00:41:52.292
Annora?

598
00:41:52.326 --> 00:41:54.727
Healer!

599
00:41:55.896 --> 00:41:57.897
(panting)

600
00:42:00.067 --> 00:42:01.267
What troubles you?

601
00:42:01.301 --> 00:42:03.669
It all troubles me.

602
00:42:03.703 --> 00:42:06.172
I know you see my angels.

603
00:42:06.206 --> 00:42:09.007
but do you see my demons.
as well?

604
00:42:09.042 --> 00:42:13.212
The ones that wrap me in fear
nearly every day now?

605
00:42:15.048 --> 00:42:17.883
We make our own demons.

606
00:42:20.653 --> 00:42:22.387
Then I'm certain
to make another.

607
00:42:31.263 --> 00:42:35.000
She's a 15-year-old girl.

608
00:42:35.034 --> 00:42:37.636
You have learned this.

609
00:42:37.670 --> 00:42:39.537
TORAN:
Wilkin!

610
00:42:41.207 --> 00:42:43.642
ANNORA:
Your brothers.

611
00:42:43.676 --> 00:42:46.310
they need you.

612
00:42:53.052 --> 00:42:55.386
Disturbing news.
brother.

613
00:42:55.420 --> 00:42:57.021
We found Ash's
trap camps

614
00:42:57.056 --> 00:42:59.390
all strewn with
blood and flesh.

615
00:42:59.424 --> 00:43:01.358
- His?
CALO: - We're not certain.

616
00:43:01.393 --> 00:43:03.628
We did find
his herb pouch.

617
00:43:03.662 --> 00:43:05.796
It tells of dread.

618
00:43:05.830 --> 00:43:08.331
God have mercy.

619
00:43:13.504 --> 00:43:15.505
(sheep bleating)

620
00:43:19.377 --> 00:43:20.711
(sheep bleats)

621
00:43:20.745 --> 00:43:22.312
Trapper!

622
00:43:23.081 --> 00:43:24.281
(bleating)

623
00:43:24.315 --> 00:43:25.683
What. ho.

624
00:43:25.717 --> 00:43:28.416
Where on God's earth
have you been?

625
00:43:28.459 --> 00:43:29.826
ASH:
West River.

626
00:43:29.860 --> 00:43:31.060
To find my girl.

627
00:43:31.094 --> 00:43:32.928
Give her a fair weather cut.

628
00:43:32.963 --> 00:43:34.930
A nap that
becomes. yea?

629
00:43:34.965 --> 00:43:38.000
Oh. I was looking for this.

630
00:43:38.034 --> 00:43:39.769
(Miriam bleats)

631
00:43:39.803 --> 00:43:41.203
Yea. I know.

632
00:43:41.238 --> 00:43:42.839
I'd lose my bobbles

633
00:43:42.873 --> 00:43:44.540
if they weren't attached
to my dingle. Heh.

634
00:43:44.574 --> 00:43:46.675
- (bleating)
- Yes. yes. I hear you.

635
00:43:53.116 --> 00:43:55.551
Mix this with water.

636
00:43:55.585 --> 00:43:56.986
Have the girl drink it

637
00:43:57.020 --> 00:44:00.056
an hour before
she meets her fate.

638
00:44:00.090 --> 00:44:01.990
It will ease the pain.

639
00:44:03.226 --> 00:44:05.660
- (Ash talks indistinctly)
- (Miriam bleats)

640
00:44:06.896 --> 00:44:08.997
Good witch.

641
00:44:09.032 --> 00:44:11.166
Mad trapper.

642
00:44:29.045 --> 00:44:30.879
Drink this.

643
00:44:32.382 --> 00:44:35.817
- (door opens)
- Do not fight me.

644
00:44:35.851 --> 00:44:37.386
Drink.

645
00:44:37.420 --> 00:44:39.821
(door closes)

646
00:44:49.099 --> 00:44:51.233
Nearly time to work your blade.

647
00:44:52.468 --> 00:44:54.870
Yea.

648
00:44:57.073 --> 00:44:58.340
Your actions
yesterday

649
00:44:58.375 --> 00:45:01.009
by the coast...

650
00:45:01.043 --> 00:45:03.412
directly offering
our lady an opinion.

651
00:45:05.815 --> 00:45:07.816
Never let that happen again.

652
00:45:10.252 --> 00:45:13.121
You come to me first.

653
00:45:13.155 --> 00:45:15.590
I will decide
if it's worthy of her ear.

654
00:45:18.961 --> 00:45:20.962
I serve the baroness.
not you.

655
00:45:20.996 --> 00:45:25.434
Gawain Maddox
serves the baroness.

656
00:45:25.468 --> 00:45:27.736
Wilkin Brattle belongs to me.

657
00:45:27.770 --> 00:45:30.971
Do not challenge me.
simple man.

658
00:45:31.005 --> 00:45:33.441
I will shred you.

659
00:45:33.475 --> 00:45:35.776
body and mind.

660
00:45:35.811 --> 00:45:37.210
I sense a growing fear

661
00:45:37.245 --> 00:45:39.747
putting on a face of boldness.

662
00:45:39.781 --> 00:45:41.949
Boldness is my most
desirable face.

663
00:45:45.587 --> 00:45:47.187
I have nothing to fear.

664
00:45:49.123 --> 00:45:52.927
Our deep secret
can cut both ways.

665
00:45:52.961 --> 00:45:55.128
Are you not a conspirator

666
00:45:55.163 --> 00:45:58.298
for keeping forbidden truth
from manor law?

667
00:45:58.333 --> 00:46:00.767
Indeed.

668
00:46:00.801 --> 00:46:02.169
We all are.

669
00:46:02.203 --> 00:46:05.839
I could lose my position.

670
00:46:05.873 --> 00:46:07.307
And you...

671
00:46:09.610 --> 00:46:11.744
your soldier.

672
00:46:11.779 --> 00:46:14.814
you new wife
and children.

673
00:46:14.849 --> 00:46:19.319
all of you will
most certainly lose your heads.

674
00:46:22.622 --> 00:46:25.458
They're ready for you. Father.

675
00:46:35.002 --> 00:46:37.370
(boys singing chant)

676
00:47:07.499 --> 00:47:09.534
(singing continues)

677
00:47:10.936 --> 00:47:13.504
(groaning quietly)

678
00:47:27.919 --> 00:47:30.354
(groaning quietly)

679
00:47:35.060 --> 00:47:37.894
(whispers)

680
00:47:46.537 --> 00:47:49.305
(singing stops. wind blowing)

681
00:47:50.974 --> 00:47:52.908
(people exclaiming)

682
00:47:54.278 --> 00:47:56.078
(Nia gasping. gagging)

683
00:47:56.112 --> 00:47:57.779
(gasping)

684
00:47:59.582 --> 00:48:01.950
(Nia moaning)

685
00:48:03.919 --> 00:48:06.321
(Nia groaning)

686
00:48:39.755 --> 00:48:41.823
Thank you. my love.

687
00:48:41.857 --> 00:48:43.124
Yea.

688
00:49:13.455 --> 00:49:15.855
♪

689
00:49:30.737 --> 00:49:33.139
(exhales)

690
00:49:33.174 --> 00:49:35.508
(moaning in pleasure)

691
00:49:43.316 --> 00:49:45.684
(moaning)

692
00:49:59.532 --> 00:50:01.400
(knock at door)

693
00:50:01.434 --> 00:50:03.335
- Come. Isabel.
- (door opens)

694
00:50:14.113 --> 00:50:16.380
Is there anything else
you need. Love?

695
00:50:16.415 --> 00:50:18.349
No.

696
00:50:18.383 --> 00:50:19.951
Thank you.

697
00:50:25.891 --> 00:50:27.992
Good night. Baroness.

698
00:50:28.027 --> 00:50:31.462
Good night. devoted maiden.

699
00:50:34.032 --> 00:50:36.033
(footsteps receding)

700
00:50:42.307 --> 00:50:43.907
(door closes)

701
00:50:57.722 --> 00:50:59.923
Oh. you two can hold
your own in the field.

702
00:50:59.958 --> 00:51:02.893
Skills learned only in battle.

703
00:51:02.927 --> 00:51:05.929
Who did you serve under?
Madog?

704
00:51:05.964 --> 00:51:08.198
We hold no ill will
against Welsh soldiers.

705
00:51:08.233 --> 00:51:09.432
(laughter)

706
00:51:09.467 --> 00:51:11.635
Especially ones we have quashed.

707
00:51:11.669 --> 00:51:13.203
(laughter)

708
00:51:13.238 --> 00:51:14.805
WILKIN:
It was another lifetime ago.

709
00:51:14.839 --> 00:51:17.274
We prefer to keep our thoughts
in the day at hand.

710
00:51:17.308 --> 00:51:20.243
TORAN: But we've heard mighty
stories of your skills.

711
00:51:20.278 --> 00:51:23.212
Some talk of a barley village
and bandits.

712
00:51:23.247 --> 00:51:25.047
- Or is that just high rumor?
NORTON: - Nay.

713
00:51:25.082 --> 00:51:26.283
I was there.

714
00:51:26.317 --> 00:51:27.917
We burned the burg.
(laughing)

715
00:51:27.951 --> 00:51:30.387
We. too...

716
00:51:30.421 --> 00:51:31.854
should keep our thoughts
in the day.

717
00:51:32.956 --> 00:51:35.825
Enjoy your drink. gentlemen.

718
00:51:45.935 --> 00:51:47.803
Sir Norton...

719
00:51:47.837 --> 00:51:50.472
the second guilt
confirmed.

720
00:51:50.507 --> 00:51:54.476
Nearly a month
to out that truth.

721
00:51:54.511 --> 00:51:56.578
Will the other three
require the same?

722
00:51:56.613 --> 00:51:58.280
If need be.

723
00:52:03.486 --> 00:52:05.321
I have your oath.

724
00:52:07.324 --> 00:52:08.957
Yea.

725
00:52:08.991 --> 00:52:10.626
The reeve will live.

726
00:52:21.871 --> 00:52:24.414
This devil will die.

727
00:52:28.026 --> 00:52:32.468
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

